\par The door of Briony Lodge was open, and an elderly woman stood upon the steps. She watched us with a sardonic eye as we stepped from the brougham. 
\par \'93Mr. Sherlock Holmes, I believe?\'94 said she. 
\par \'93I am Mr. Holmes,\'94 answered my companion, looking at her with a questioning and rather startled gaze. 
\par \'93Indeed! My mistress told me that you were likely to call. She left this morning with her husband by the 5:15 train from Charing Cross for the Continent.\'94 
\par \'93What!\'94 Sherlock Holmes staggered back, white with chagrin and surprise. \'93Do you mean that she has left England?\'94 
\par \'93Never to return.\'94 
\par \'93And the papers?\'94 asked the King hoarsely. \'93All is lost.\'94 
