\par }\pard \s16\qj \fi480\li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3304115 {\insrsid3304115 \'93What a woman\emdash oh, what a woman!\'94 cried the King of Bohemia, when we had all three read this epistle. \'93
Did I not tell you how quick and resolute she was? Would she not have made an admirable queen? Is it not a pity that she was not on my level?\'94 
\par \'93From what I have seen of the lady, she seems, indeed, to be on a very different level to your Majesty,\'94 said Holmes coldly. \'93I am sorry that I have not been able to bring your Majesty\rquote s business to a more successful conclusion.\'94 

\par \'93On the contrary, my dear sir,\'94 cried the King; \'93nothing could be more successful. I know that her word is inviolate. The photograph is now as safe as if it were in the fire.\'94 
\par \'93I am glad to hear your Majesty say so.\'94 
\par \'93I am immensely indebted to you. Pray tell me in what way I can reward you. This ring\emdash \'94 He slipped an emerald snake ring from his finger and held it out upon the palm of his hand. 
\par \'93Your Majesty has something which I should value even more highly,\'94 said Holmes. 
\par \'93You have but to name it.\'94 
\par \'93This photograph!\'94 
\par The King stared at him in amazement. 
\par \'93Irene\rquote s photograph!\'94 he cried. \'93Certainly, if you wish it.\'94 
\par }\pard \s16\qj \fi480\li0\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3304115 {\insrsid3304115 \'93I thank your Majesty. Then there is no more to be done in the matter. I have the honour to wish you a very good morning.
\'94 He bowed, and, turning away without observing the hand which the King had stretched out to him, he set off in my company for his chambers. 
