\par \'93Pray continue,\'94 said Holmes. \'93Your narrative promises to be a most interesting one.\'94 
\par \'93You will find it rather disconnected, I fear, and there may prove to be little relation between the different incidents of which I spea
k. On the very first day that I was at the Copper Beeches, Mr. Rucastle took me to a small outhouse which stands near the kitchen door. As we approached it I heard the sharp rattling of a chain, and the sound as of a large animal moving about. 
\par \'93\~\lquote Look in here!\rquote  said Mr. Rucastle, showing me a slit between two planks. \lquote Is he not a beauty?\rquote  
\par \'93I looked through and was conscious of two glowing eyes, and of a vague figure huddled up in the darkness. 
\par \'93\~\lquote Don\rquote t be frightened,\rquote  said my employer, laughing at the start which I had given. \lquote It\rquote 
